<br>
Next time a cop wants to give you a speeding ticket and you know you weren't speeding or at least are sure he didn't get you on radar, ask to see the gun reading...if they can't produce it, the ticket won't stick.<br>
<br>
And the advice of bringing a parent and/or lawyer along (preferably both) to your court date was pretty solid...chances are pretty decent you'll get out of the ticket if you show maturity and enough responsibility to show up with at least a parent to argue for you with the judge/DA. Show up in a dress shirt/slacks/dress shows/tie. Consider a sports coat as well. Yeah, it does make a difference...I've sat in traffic court and watched little Timmy in his ripped up Metallica T-shirt and dirty jeans get $150 + driving school while I get a &quot;bad boy, don't do it again&quot; probation, and I was going faster. Attitude and appearance mean alot in traffic court, especially when you're under 20. <p><table border=1>
