G <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uryotv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RyotV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>1st post by this guy</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/30/02 5:18:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3635.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about cops/law/driving</span><hr size=1> Well, I am Canadian but dealing with the law is similar.<br>
<br>
A couple of tips.<br>
<br>
1) You have the right to question your accuser. Bring a list of<br>
questions to court . Try not to ask questions you don't know the<br>
answer to.<br>
<br>
Samples:<br>
(bring a large diagram of the parking lot and show which way<br>
you were driving at the time)<br>
a) What exactly did the officer see that prompted him to <br>
give you a ticket?<br>
b)Where exactly (and point to your diagram) was he positioned that he could see what happened and what direction was he facing?<br>
<br>
These kinds of questions lay a foundation of what exactly happened.<br>
<br>
2) About the approximate time that this happened, go back to the parking lot and take pictures. Lots of them. Show what the<br>
lighting was like, how dark it was etc..<br>
<br>
3) He claims you were abve the speed limit. How can he prove this? Did he have a radar unit functioning? Was he stationary or pacing you? If not, have that part of the ticket rescinded.<br>
<br>
4) Do not be afraid or nervous if you can. The system of laws is not there to intimidate you. Be brave, polite and look people in the eye.<br>
<br>
5) The suggestion of bringing witnesses is very good, but you have to make sure youi know what they will say if asked any questions. If it doesn't help your case, then don't bring them.<br>
A parent would help as well. Shows you have family support.<br>
<br>
<br>
Thats what I can think of off the top of my head.<br>
<br>
Ryot/Vaylo/Banouin<br>
