<br>
Same thing happened to me when I was a nOOb driver.<br>
<br>
Friend went to grab my nipple (titty twister), and I crossed the double yellow line.  No other traffic, just my car.  Well, and the cop who was at the next light.  He pulled me over, asked for my info, told me what I did wrong, and I gave the &quot;rolling of the eyes&quot; as I turned around.<br>
<br>
He was a nice cop, explained that if I had just given him the info, and not the attitude, I would have gotten the warning.  Instead I got the 10mph over ticket, and the wreckless driving tix for crossing the line.  Told the judge what happened, I could tell he wanted to laugh when I told him about the titty twister, he said pay the speeding ticket and dropped the wreckless driving charge.  No loss of licence, just increased insurance rates.<br>
<br>
If you really hadn't been doing anything wrong, the cop would have let you go with a warning, or wouldn't have pulled you over at all.  Your buddy is a jerk, he broke the law, beat his ass.  I guarantee you mouthed off to the cop when he pulled you over, &quot;I Wasn't Speeding, I was doing 28 in a 25&quot;  or something like that, its a guaranteed ticket everytime.<br>
<br>
Future reference, &quot;Yes Sir, No Sir&quot;, &quot;here is my information Sir&quot;, these are acceptable answers to officers questions.<br>
<br>
When he pulled you over, your first comment should have been an apology for your friends action, and your friend should have apologised for being a moron.  I bet the cop would have issued you a warning and called it a night.<br>
<br>
Pay the fine, lose your licence, and learn your lesson.<br>
<br>
1) A parking lot is no place to screw around.<br>
2) You are responsible for the actions of your passengers.<br>
3) Never give a smart ass answer to a cop.<br>
<br>
Get mom and dad and the family lawyer, go to court, see the judge, pay the fine and ask that your licence not be suspended because it's your first offence.  Be sure to wear a shirt and a tie, and not sneakers.<br>
<br>
(police can issue you a ticket for speeding if there is sufficient evidence to suggest that you were.  If he gave you a ticket for going 30 miles above the limit, then he would need to produce supporting evidence.  His credibilty as a professional law enforcement official will always win out in the &quot;my word against your word&quot; scenario.) <p><img src = "http://home.maine.rr.com/waassaap/newtag.gif""http://home.maine.rr.com/waassaap/New5.gif'></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ujorlenrizzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jorlen Rizzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>no title</span><br>  Posts: 389<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/30/02 9:33:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3635.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about cops/law/driving</span><hr size=1> Take it to court man.  Fuck that shit.  What chances you have if you don't?  None.  What chances do you have if you go?  Well, if you set yourself up properly and make a good impression and have valuable arguments, you have a GOOD chance of winning.<br>
